President Muhammadu Buhari has scheduled to visit Ogun State on Thursday, January 13, after the December 21, 2019 scheduled visit was not made.
The Chief Press Secretary to Ogun State Governor, Kunle Somorin, in a statement on Sunday noted that President Buhari would have visited Ogun State on December 21, 2021, but the visit was canceled.  The CPS stated that President Buhari is expected to make the rescheduled visit to Ogun State, Southwest Nigeria on Thursday.
The CPS indicated that the President would inaugurate some infrastructural projects executed by Governor Abiodun during the visit.
According to the statement: “The President will be welcomed at the Gateway City Gate Monument Park, Sagamu Interchange, at 10.00a.m, where the first project will be commissioned by him.
“Apart from the Gateway City Gate, other projects expected to be inaugurated by President Buhari include Ijebu-Ode Mojoda-Epe expressway and two housing estates – the 527-Unit low and Medium Kobape Housing scheme Kobape and the Highbrow, 83 duplexes at Kings Court Estate at Oke Mosan, Abeokuta.”
